article.headline: CS Northridge 99, Pepperdine 64
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Deon Tresvant scored 25 points and Willie Galick added 14 points and 10 rebounds to lead Cal State Northridge past Pepperdine 99-64 Thursday. Northridge (3-6) took control with a 25-3 run in the first half to hand the Waves' their 10th straight loss. Tresvant helped Northridge pad the lead in the second half by scoring eight straight points. He finished 10-for-17 from the floor and hit five 3s. Lorne Jackson and Keion Bell led Pepperdine (1-10) with 13 points apiece, and Taylor Darby added 10 points and 14 rebounds. The Waves led 13-8 early in the game but missed their next 13 of 14 shots and trailed 47-24 at halftime. Pepperdine's losing streak is its longest since it dropped the last eight games of the 2005-06 season and the first two of 2006-07.
